    <div class="text">
      <p>Chances are your day doesn't revolve around your body's natural time clock - circadian rhythms. Unfortunately our daily routine is often the opposite of what our bodies and minds are wired to do. &nbsp;Circadian Rhythm disruptions are linked to a host of medical conditions including obesity, dementia, diabetes, and depression. Here's a breakdown of the ideal times to perform certain activities based on your natural timeline. &nbsp;</p>
